is.erle.mavlink

Class XMLParamParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • is.erle.mavlink.XMLParamParser

  • public class XMLParamParser
extends java.lang.Object
    This class processes the ParameterData.xml file for the required information. It has utility functions to read the xml file and then parse it into a map, a string or a range of values.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Version:
    %I%, %G%
    Author:
    Abhay Kumar

      • getParamDataXml

        public java.lang.String getParamDataXml(java.lang.String nodeKey,
                                        java.lang.String metaKey,
                                        java.lang.String vehicleType)
        It processes the xmlDocument to return the string contained for a given nodeKey,metaKey and vehicleType
        Parameters:
        nodeKey - Name of the node queried like "FLTMODE1"
        metaKey - Name of the subnode or metakey inside this node whose value is being queried.
        vehicleType - Type of the vehicle to look for this node.
        Returns:
        String contained within the metakey of the xmlDocument

      • getParamOptions

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Short> getParamOptions(java.lang.String nodeKey,
                                                                           java.lang.String vehicleType)
        It processes the xmlDocument to return a HashMap containing the parameter options for a given nodeKey and vehicleType. The metakey used here is VALUES
        Parameters:
        nodeKey - Name of the node queried like "FLTMODE1"
        vehicleType - Type of the vehicle to look for this node.
        Returns:
        Parameter options for the given node and vehicle type xmlDocument

      • getParamRebootRequired

        public boolean getParamRebootRequired(java.lang.String nodeKey,
                                      java.lang.String vehicleType)
        It processes the xmlDocument to return whether a reboot is required or not. The metakey used here is REBOOTREQUIRED
        Parameters:
        nodeKey - Name of the node queried
        vehicleType - Type of the vehicle to look for this node.
        Returns:
        true if reboot is required for the given node key; otherwise false

      • getParamRange

        public MinMaxPair<java.lang.Float> getParamRange(java.lang.String nodeKey,
                                                 java.lang.String vehicleType)
        It processes the xmlDocument to return a pair containing the parameter range for a given nodeKey and vehicleType. The metakey used here is RANGE
        Parameters:
        nodeKey - Name of the node queried
        vehicleType - Type of the vehicle to look for this node.
        Returns:
        Minimum and Maximum value of a parameter.
